DESCRIPTION:Explore an imaginative\, immersive installation that transfor
 ms the museum into a vibrant\, crocheted\, underwater ecosystem inspired 
 by Indonesia's spectacular coral reefs. Explore colorful coral reefs\, pl
 ayful fish\, and fantastical sea creatures â€” all meticulously hand-knit
  and crocheted. Read more about this featured exhibition. (https://artmus
 eum.indiana.edu/exhibitions/current/_feature-exhibitions/2026-02-07-mulya
 na-vital-ecosystems.html)Step into the world of acclaimed photographer Ra
 nia Matar (b. 1964\, Lebanon)\, whose striking portraits document young w
 omen persisting in uncertain times. Matar's lens highlights women's creat
 ivity\, strength\, dignity\, and resilienceâ€”offering a powerful counter
 -narrative to the challenges of her country and region. Read more about t
 his featured exhibition (https://artmuseum.indiana.edu/exhibitions/upcomi
 ng/_feature-exhibitions/2026-03-05-rania-matar-where-do-i-go.html).  &#16
 0\;  Know Before You GoSpace is available for the first 12 people to chec
 k in with Guest Services on the day. Drop by the information desk on the 
 first floor of the museum when you arrive.A small handbag may be carried 
 at your side. Backpacks and large bags will need to be stored before tour
 ing. Learn more aboutmuseum guidelines.If you park in the IMU parking lot
 \, Guest Services can validate your parking voucher for a discount.Read a
 boutwhere to find us and where to park\,
